<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 22 at 6:14PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of southwestern Blaine
County through 645 PM MDT...
At 614 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 24
miles west of Hays, or 29 miles west of Zortman, moving east at 10
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southwestern Blaine
County.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
